        <abstract> 
<p>Comments on review of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> by Andrew Murray [<hi rend="italic">Proc. R. Soc. Edinburgh</hi> 4 (1860): 274–91] and views of William Hopkins on <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> ["Physical theories and the phenomena of life" <hi rend="italic">Fraser’s Mag.</hi> 61 (1860): 739–52; 62 (1860): 74–90]. The attacks will tell heavily.</p> 
            <p>Mentions Blyth’s failure to receive appointment as naturalist to China expedition of 1860.</p>
            <p>Encloses letter from Asa Gray.</p>
            <p>Discusses gestation period in domesticated dogs.</p>
            <p>Comments on hybrid fertility.</p>
        </abstract>
